      Convert a Shesmu JSON value into a Jackson structure

      Note that the converted JSON object must not be mutated by the recipient or the olive might break as olives assume all values are immutable.

    • dictionary

      public static <K, V> TypeGuarantee<Map<K,V>> dictionary(TypeGuarantee<K> key, TypeGuarantee<V> value)
      Provides an argument mapping from a Shesmu dictionary/map into a Java map
      Parameters:
      key - the type guarantee for the keys; note that the conversion should preserve equality of the original values (i.e., if two keys are not equal in Shesmu, then K should also be not equal) or collisions could occur
      value - the type guarantee for the values
      Returns:
      a guarantee for a map
